---
source: crates/loom/tests/cli_help.rs
expression: "loom_help(&[\"gate\"])"
---
Quality gate — annotation-dispatched verifiers and LLM rubric

Usage: loom gate [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]

Commands:
  audit   Run every deterministic verifier followed by the LLM rubric (`verify` then `review`). The full PR-gate path
  verify  Run every `[check]` / `[test]` / `[system]` verifier — cheap relative to review, expensive relative to status
  check   Run only `[check]`-tier verifiers (static analysis). Fastest tier
  test    Run only `[test]`-tier verifiers, batched into one runner subprocess
  system  Run only `[system]`-tier verifiers (containers, packaging, end-to-end). Slow
  review  Run the LLM rubric — criterion-attached judges plus the rubric walk over the diff. Expensive
  judge   Run only criterion-attached `[judge]` verifiers — skips the rubric walk
  rubric  Run only the rubric walk over the diff — skips criterion-attached judges
  help    Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -w, --workspace <PATH>  Workspace root. Defaults to the current working directory
  -A, --agent <BACKEND>   Override the agent backend for this invocation [possible values: claude, pi]
  -h, --help              Print help
